# shadcn/ui Component Usage Guidelines

Follow these guidelines when using shadcn/ui components to maintain consistency and proper implementation patterns.

## Component Location & Imports

All shadcn/ui components are located in `src/components/ui/` and should be imported using absolute paths:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - Use absolute imports
import { Button } from '@/src/components/ui/button'
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '@/src/components/ui/card'
import { Input } from '@/src/components/ui/input'

// ❌ Bad - Don't use relative imports
import { Button } from '../ui/button'
import { Card } from './ui/card'
```

## Styling Guidelines

### 1. Use CSS Variables & Design Tokens

Always use the built-in CSS variables for colors and spacing:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - Use semantic color classes
<div className="bg-background text-foreground border-border">
<Button className="text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">

// ❌ Bad - Don't use arbitrary colors
<div className="bg-white text-black border-gray-200">
<Button className="text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-900">
```

**Common design tokens:**
- `background`, `foreground` - Main background and text
- `muted`, `muted-foreground` - Subtle backgrounds and text
- `border` - Border colors
- `primary`, `primary-foreground` - Primary brand colors
- `destructive`, `destructive-foreground` - Error/danger colors

### 2. Component Composition

Extend components using the `cn()` utility and className prop:

```typescript
// ✅ Good - Extend with additional classes
<Button 
  variant="outline" 
  className={cn("w-full justify-start", isActive && "bg-accent")}
>
  Custom Button
</Button>

// ✅ Good - Conditional styling
<Card className={cn("transition-all", isSelected && "ring-2 ring-primary")}>
```

## Component Patterns

### 1. Loading States

Use Skeleton component for loading states:

```typescript
import { Skeleton } from '@/src/components/ui/skeleton'

// Loading card
<Card>
  <CardHeader>
    <Skeleton className="h-4 w-[250px]" />
    <Skeleton className="h-4 w-[200px]" />
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <Skeleton className="h-[125px] w-full" />
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Don't mix styling approaches** - Use either shadcn classes OR custom Tailwind, not both

## Adding New shadcn Components

When adding new shadcn components to the project:

1. **Use the CLI**: `npx shadcn-ui add [component-name]`
2. **Check dependencies**: Ensure all required packages are installed
3. **Update imports**: Use absolute path imports in your components
